Chosen: ship the four overflow layouts as a settings-selectable mode, plus a None mode (the
default) that keeps the classic single ring so existing wheels are unchanged. A settings field
lets the user set the threshold — how many tiles the main ring holds before the extra ring
appears. Below the threshold every mode renders one ring. Modes: None (default), Overflow band
(inner ring stays familiar until the cap), Split balanced, Petals, Concentric columns. Verified
against the docs/demo baseline across all four themes; the overflow ring always flows outward to
keep the drop target large.
